        "en": "<p>The Flemish support subsidy (Dutch: Vlaamse ondersteuningspremie/VOP) is a subsidy for employers who hire or have hired a person with a work-limiting disability. The VOP is intended to compensate for any additional costs and lower productivity caused by the work-limiting disability. In this way, the Flemish authorities want to make it more attractive for employers to hire or retain people with a work-limiting disability.</p>",
